metadata.name: Duel on a Moonlit Night
metadata.description:
The two-tailed cat ”Nekomata” is a yokai that originated from a long-lived domestic cat's transformation.
The nine-tailed fox is also a yokai known in China and other Asian countries.
Both of them have been beloved in Japan since ancient times.
After people have gone to sleep, the two yokai engage in a duel on the rooftops of the town.
Their weapons are only musical instruments! It's a battle of sound.

*The artwork incorporates some modified ukiyo-e prints from the Edo period as the background.
We are striving to create "New Ukiyo-e" 
while cherishing the essence of traditional Ukiyo-e, 
we want to spread the fun and new charm of its to the  world!
